articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Kyiv and its European allies demanded that they be included in any peace negotiations, after U.S. President Donald Trump spoke by phone with Russia's Vladimir Putin and said Ukraine could neither have all of its land back nor join NATO.
articles.title: EU warns against 'dirty deal' on Ukraine after Trump-Putin phone call

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A car drove into a crowd in Munich on Thursday injuring several people, police said, as the southern German city prepares for a top-level security conference due to be attended by U.S. Vice President JD Vance and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy.
articles.title: Several injured after car drives into crowd of people in Munich

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, James Mackenzie
articles.description: The Palestinian militant group Hamas signalled that a crisis threatening to unravel the Gaza ceasefire deal could be avoided despite uncertainty over the number of hostages due to be released on Saturday and disagreements over aid supplies.
articles.title: Hamas says it is willing to move ahead with Gaza ceasefire

articles.author: Andrew Gray, Lili Bayer, Phil Stewart, Idrees Ali
articles.description: U.S. Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth rejected criticism on Thursday of Washington's negotiating strategy with Russia on the war in Ukraine and warned Europe against treating America like a "sucker" by making it responsible for its defense.
articles.title: Europe can't turn Uncle Sam into 'Uncle Sucker,' US defense secretary says

articles.author: Andrea Shalal, David Lawder, Susan Heavey
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump said he plans to unveil reciprocal tariffs on Thursday afternoon but gave no details about his latest tariff plan, which could take aim at every country that charges duties on U.S. imports.
articles.title: Trump says reciprocal tariffs coming on Thursday

articles.author: Yurii Kovalenko, Dan Peleschuk
articles.description: Ukrainians braced on Thursday for a hopeful but perilous phase of their war with Russia after U.S. President Donald Trump's phone call with Vladimir Putin stirred fears his move to swiftly end the fighting could cost Ukraine dearly.
articles.title: Ukrainians brace for perilous diplomacy with Trump focused on ending war
US embassies told to prepare for staff cuts as Trump overhauls diplomatic corps, sources say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thailand has received 260 human trafficking victims, more than half of them Ethiopians, from Myanmar, its army said on Thursday, in a massive repatriation that comes amid a mounting crackdown on scam centres operating along a porous border.
articles.title: Thailand receives 260 victims of human trafficking from Myanmar, army says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thousands of Belgians took to the streets on Thursday in protest over the new government's planned pension reforms in the first day of a multi-day strike that halted all air traffic in the country.
articles.title: Anti-government protest halts air traffic in Belgium

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Alexander Vinnik, a Russian national convicted of cyber crime and released by U.S. authorities as part of an exchange of prisoners, arrived in Moscow late on Thursday, Russian news agencies quoted aviation officials as saying.
articles.title: Plane carrying Alexander Vinnik, released by US in prisoner swap, arrives in Moscow, agencies say
